description: The user clicked the mouse on the desktop background.
The user clicked on the "Properties" option in the right-click context menu. As a result, the "Display Properties" window opened.
outcome: A "Display Properties" window appeared, and the mouse cursor changed to an hourglass icon, suggesting ongoing system processing. The previously mentioned right-click context menu is not visible.

event: The mouse clicked on Themes DesktopScreenaverAppearanceSettings.
description: The user clicked on the "Screen Saver" tab within the "Display Properties" window. As a result, the content area of the window updated to display the "Screen Saver" tab's options.
outcome: The UI updated to display the "Screen Saver" tab within the "Display Properties" window.  The content area now includes a screen saver selection dropdown (currently set to "Windows XP"), a wait time setting, a preview window showing the selected screensaver, and controls related to monitor power settings. The "Apply" button at the bottom of the window became active.

description: The user clicked the **Screen Saver** dropdown menu. As a result, the selected option changed to **(None)**, and a pop-up window titled "Keep your computer up to date" appeared.
outcome: The selected screensaver in the Screen Saver Dropdown Menu changed to "(None)" from "Windows XP."  Simultaneously, a yellow pop-up window titled "Keep your computer up to date" appeared at the bottom of the screen.

description: The user clicked on the "None" option in the "Screen Saver" dropdown menu. As a result, the dropdown menu closed, the "Wait" time changed to "10" minutes, and a pop-up notification appeared in the bottom right corner of the screen.
outcome: A pop-up notification reading "Keep your computer up to date" appeared in the bottom right corner of the screen.  Concurrently, the displayed "Wait" time changed to "10" minutes and the "Screen Saver" dropdown menu closed.

description: The user clicked the "Power..." button within the "Monitor power" section of the "Display Properties" window. As a result, the "Power Options Properties" window appeared, causing the "Display Properties" window to become temporarily inaccessible.
outcome: A new window titled "Power Options Properties" opened in front of the "Display Properties" window.  The new window contains a "Power schemes" dropdown menu (currently empty) and an hourglass icon, suggesting loading content.  During this loading, the "Display Properties" window became partially unusable: its "OK", "Cancel", and "Apply" buttons are hidden, and the "Screen Saver" tab is inactive. Additionally, a system notification about keeping the computer updated appeared.

event: The mouse clicked on Home/Office Desk.
description: The user clicked the "Home/Office Desk" option within the "Power schemes" dropdown menu. As a result, the selected power scheme changed to "Always On" and the "Turn off monitor" setting updated to "After 20 mins".
outcome: The power scheme changed to "Always On" and the monitor timeout setting updated to "After 20 mins."

description: The user clicked on the "System hibernates" label within the "Power Options Properties" window.  This action resulted in the expansion of the "System hibernates" dropdown menu, revealing a list of time options, with "After 5 hours" currently selected.  Additionally, the "Turn off monitor", "Turn off hard disks", and "System standby" options, previously set to "Never", were replaced with dropdown menus displaying time ranges.
outcome: A pop-up window titled "Keep your computer up to date" appeared in the bottom left corner of the screen.  Concurrently, the "System hibernates" dropdown menu expanded to reveal time options, with "After 5 hours" selected. The dropdown menus for "Turn off monitor", "Turn off hard disks", and "System standby" similarly replaced their "Never" options with time ranges.

description: The user clicked the information icon located next to the "System standby" option in the "Settings for Always On power scheme" section of the "Power Options Properties" window. This action resulted in a pop-up box titled "Keep your computer up to date" appearing in the bottom right corner of the screen.
outcome: A pop-up box titled "Keep your computer up to date" appeared in the bottom right corner of the screen. The pop-up contains an information icon, a message suggesting automatic updates, and a close button.

description: The user clicked the "Apply" button at the bottom of the "Power Options Properties" window. As a result, a yellow pop-up notification with the message "Keep your computer up to date" appeared in the bottom right corner of the screen, and the visual highlighting was removed from the "OK" button.
outcome: A yellow pop-up notification with the message "Keep your computer up to date" appeared in the bottom right corner of the screen.  Concurrently, the visual highlighting was removed from the "OK" button.

description: The user clicked the mouse on an element outside the "Power Options Properties" window. As a result, the active window focus changed to the "Display Properties" window, with the "Screen Saver" tab in view.
outcome: The "Display Properties" window came into focus, with the "Screen Saver" tab selected.

description: The user clicked the "OK" button at the bottom of the "Display Properties" window.  As a result, the "Display Properties" window closed.
